TY  - JOUR
TI  - Long Cheap Talk
AU  - Aumann, Robert J.
AU  - Hart, Sergiu
AB  - [With cheap talk, more can be achieved by long conversations than by a single message--even when one side is strictly better informed than the other. ("Cheap talk" means plain conversation--unmediated, nonbinding, and payoff-irrelevant.) This work characterizes the equilibrium payoffs for all two-person games in which one side is better informed than the other and cheap talk is permitted.]
C1  - Full publication date: Nov., 2003
